    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{3}{r-1}-\frac{6r}{r^{2}-1}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{3}{r+1}, r\ne 1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{3}{r-1}-\frac{6r}{r^{2}-1}} 
      \amp = {\frac{3}{r-1}}-\frac{6 r}{(r - 1)(r + 1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{3\cdot({r+1})}{({r-1})\cdot({r+1})} -\frac{6 r}{(r - 1)(r + 1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{3\mathopen{}\left(r+1\right)-6r}}{(r - 1)(r + 1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{3r+3-6r}}{(r - 1)(r + 1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-3r+3}}{(r - 1)(r + 1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-3\mathopen{}\left(r-1\right)}}{(r - 1)(r + 1)} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{3}{r+1}, r\ne 1}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{r-1}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>r \ne {1}</m>.</p>
</solution>
